---
const axes = [
  { term: "External validity", note: "does it survive a new population?" },
  { term: "Subgroup fairness", note: "who pays for the average?" },
  { term: "Calibration", note: "are the probabilities honest?" },
  { term: "Shift diagnosis", note: "which failure, before labels arrive?" },
  { term: "Deployment discipline", note: "when should the gate stay closed?" },
];
---

<section class="vision container" id="research" data-reveal>
  <p class="label-mono section-eyebrow">Research vision</p>
  <div class="vision-grid">
    <p class="vision-statement">
      A model can be accurate, and the decision it drives can still be <em>unfair, miscalibrated, and invalid</em> for the people it meets in
      deployment. My research asks the question benchmarks skip: not <span class="q">“is it accurate?”</span> but <span class="q">“does the decision remain fair, calibrated, externally
      valid, private, and economically deployable — under real constraints?”</span>
    </p>
    <ul class="vision-axes">
      {
        axes.map((a) => (
          <li>
            <span class="axis-term">{a.term}</span>
            <span class="axis-note">{a.note}</span>
          </li>
        ))
      }
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .vision {
    padding-block: var(--space-section);
    border-bottom: var(--rule);
  }

  .section-eyebrow {
    color: var(--signal);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
    display: block;
  }

  .vision-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 7fr) minmax(0, 4fr);
    gap: var(--space-16);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .vision-statement {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    line-height: 1.42;
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-tight);
    max-width: none;
  }

  .vision-statement em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--signal);
  }

  .q { color: var(--ink-2); }

  .vision-axes {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    border-top: 2px solid var(--ink);
  }

  .vision-axes li {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-1);
    padding-block: var(--space-4);
    border-bottom: var(--rule);
  }

  .axis-term {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .axis-note {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--ink-3);
  }

  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .vision-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: var(--space-12); }
  }
</style>
